formulas.expression:
IF(ISBLANK({!curHouseEquity}), "",
    IF({!curHouseEquity} = 0, "They have no equity in the house",
        "They have " & TEXT({!curHouseEquity}) & " in the house"
    )
)

IF(ISBLANK({!currAmountOfSavings}), "",
    IF({!currAmountOfSavings} = 0, "They have no savings",
        "They have " & TEXT({!currAmountOfSavings}) & " in savings"
    )
)

IF(ISBLANK({!currAmountOfValueInStocks}), "",
    IF({!currAmountOfValueInStocks} = 0, "They have no value in stocks",
        "They have " & TEXT({!currAmountOfValueInStocks}) & " in stocks"
    )
)

textTemplates.text:
When provided with a set of answers to the outlined questions, your task is to create a comprehensive profile of the customer or couple. The profile should provide a clear, concise, and engaging summary of their situation, motivations, and relevant financial details. Follow the instructions below to ensure consistency and completeness in your profile creation. 

The Respone will be shown on the last page of a screenflow in Salesforce and in a Rich Text field on an object in Salesforce, so separate it nicely into paragraphs, etc. but make sure to only use HTML that is being read correctly by a rich-text field in Salesforce - I dont want weird code remaining in the field.
While you will essentially list answers to the questions, do it while story-telling a bit about the couple. Dont come up with things that arent there, but make it engaging.

Language:
If Market Unit is DFJ_DK or Testamente_DK you reply in Danish
If Market Unit is FA_SE or Testamente_SV you reply in Swedish
You never reply in English
Market Unit: {!Get_Lead.Market_Unit__c}

Instructions for Creating the Profile: 
Introduction:
Begin with a brief introduction that includes the reason they signed up and how long they have been considering it. Mention any key motivations and why they decided to take action now.
Personal Details:
Include personal details such as names, ages, marital status, and work situations for both individuals if applicable.
Family Information:
Mention the presence of children and their status (age and biological/blended). Include information about grandchildren if relevant. 
Information about children (disregard if empty, but tell a bit about them if there is one or more children): {!varChildInfo}
Property and Assets:
Detail their homeownership status, including deed distribution and approximate equity in the house.
Note the ownership of any vacation homes, cars, savings, and stocks, including approximate values where provided.
Financial Expectations and Plans:
Include any expectations of inheritance and differences in individual fortunes. The fortune skew is meassured like this: They have equal fortunes if it is 0. Person 1 owns everything if it is -100 and person 2 owns everything if it is 100. Values between this, indicate which person owns more.
Mention the presence of pension plans, ability to move them, and their approximate values if applicable.
Insurances and other information: Tell about their insurances and if they have any large pets.

